"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/completely-mad-review-across-the-ocean-with-an-oar-5afb65c0"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823324?width=639&amp;height=947" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">飞马座</span></div></div></div><p><strong>作者：詹姆斯·R·汉森</strong><em>飞马座</em></p><p>汤姆·麦克莱恩面临着冻伤、不间断的大风和看起来像摩天大楼的海浪。一条 15 英尺长的鲨鱼跟着他好几天了。他给它取名为“蓝”。比尔·希维评论。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/completely-mad-review-across-the-ocean-with-an-oar-5afb65c0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阅读评论</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-controversialist-review-mixing-it-up-with-martin-peretz-814b0ba4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">有争议的人：与所有人、左派、右派和中间派的争论</a></h3><div class="media-object scope-
